.TH GTI 1 "January 2026" "GTI" "Typing Test Application"
.SH NAME
gti \- fast, lightweight, terminal-based typing speed and practice application
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gti
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B GTI
is a command-line typing test application designed for improving typing speed and accuracy. It provides various practice modes including timed tests, progressive challenges, custom text files, and random quotes. Track your progress with detailed statistics and customize your experience with multiple themes and language support.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B gti
Start practice mode
.TP
.B gti quote
Start with random quotes
.TP
.B gti challenge
Progressive challenge with levels
.TP
.B gti statistics
View detailed typing statistics
.TP
.B gti theme
Manage color themes
.TP
.B gti config
View and manage configuration
.TP
.B gti version
Display version information
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-chunks <count>
Number of chunks per group (default: 2)
.TP
.B \-g, \-\-groups <count>
Number of groups (default: 1)
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-custom <file>
Start with custom text file
.TP
.B \-\-start <num>
Start from paragraph number (for custom mode)
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-timed <time>
Start timed mode (e.g., 30, 10s, 5m)
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-language <lang>
Language for word generation
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-shortcuts
Show shortcuts and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B gti
Start practice mode (2 chunks)
.TP
.B gti \-n 10
Practice with 10 chunks per group
.TP
.B gti \-t 30
Start 30-second timed test
.TP
.B gti \-c mytext.txt
Practice with custom text file
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
Ctrl+C
Force quit application
.TP
Ctrl+Q
Quit with confirmation
.TP
Tab/Enter
Submit completed text
.TP
Ctrl+R
Restart current session
.TP
Esc
Close overlays/Cancel operations
.SH SUPPORTED LANGUAGES
GTI supports 25+ languages for practice: English, Spanish, French, German, Japanese, Russian, Italian, Portuguese, Chinese, Arabic, Hindi, Korean, Dutch, Swedish, Czech, Danish, Finnish, Greek, Hebrew, Hungarian, Norwegian, Polish, Thai, Turkish.
.SH THEMES
GTI supports 25+ color themes for terminal customization, including default, dracula, solarized, and many more.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GTI_CONFIG_DIR
Directory for configuration files (defaults to system config directory)
.TP
.B GTI_THEME
Default theme to use
.SH FILES
Configuration files are stored in the user's config directory.
